folder: Piers 102, 103, 104 - 60th, 61st, and 62nd Streets - [Welfare Island]., Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
East River, showing (left to right) piers 102, 103, and 104, off York Ave., at the foot of East 60th, 61st and 62nd Streets, respectively. Also shown is a general view westward of the surrounding area.
April 5, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A close-up of pier 104, as viewed in a northerly direction from pier 103. On the right is visible the northern half of Welfare Island.
September 23, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
title: East River - Manhattan - Piers 102, 103, 104 - 60th, 61st, and 62nd Streets - [Welfare Island].
